reviews.review_text:
First show This was my first Dead show as a young teenager. The only thing I regret is not catching the Dead in the years before. I blame my parents....!

This show rocked and as a 17 year old was not only eye opening it was mind altering.

I was there. I had seen the band quite a few times, but this was really the first run I went to on my own, just me, with my own money, just going to see who I'd meet and what would happen. It was fairly epic, and I actually compare the story to Fear & Loathing in Las Vegas, but I'll never tell it. The lightning was amazing, both this first day and the second. On this, we got chased out of the stadium at the end of the show by a sandstorm. I was with an amazingly beautiful lady from Cali to whom I'd given a ticket to her first Dead show. I'm glad it was a good show, as opposed to the kind of show they played on the third day. But it doesn't compare to day 2.

Good times This was a fun show, the rain and lightening in the background and all the strange weather events. Looks like rain, it started raining a little bit right after that and a rainbow. Magical times!
